{"itemid":1566,"subject":"Carrie Is Coming","event":"We have another cool author event Monday night at the Jean Cocteau.\r\n\r\nCARRIE VAUGHN will be driving down to Denver to join us for the evening.&nbsp; We&#39;ll be having an hour of conversation and taking some questions from the audience, after which we&#39;ll adjourn to the lobby so Carrie can sign books.\r\n\r\n<img alt=\"carrie\" src=\"http://ic.pics.livejournal.com/grrm/7059164/231055/231055_900.jpg\" title=\"carrie\" /><img alt=\"low mid\" src=\"http://ic.pics.livejournal.com/grrm/7059164/231247/231247_900.jpg\" title=\"low mid\" />\r\n\r\nCarrie is best known as the author of the bestselling urban fantasy series KITTY AND THE MIDNIGHT HOUR and its many sequels, about the adventures of a werewolf talk show host.&nbsp; LOW MIDNIGHT, her newest book, is a spinoff of sorts from the Kitty series, featuring one of the most popular of Kitty&#39;s supporting cast.\r\n\r\nShe has also been one of the mainstays of the revived Wild Cards series, creator of Earth Witch and Curveball and the whole<b><i> American Hero</i></b> concept that launched the &quot;next generation&quot; WC books in INSIDE STRAIGHT.&nbsp; If you haven&#39;t sampled any of her Wild Cards work, check out her Earth Witch story on Tor.com: http://www.tor.com/stories/2014/10/nuestra-senora-de-la-esperanza-carrie-vaughn\r\n\r\nShe also has her own &quot;superpowers&quot; universe, as seem in AFTER THE GOLDEN AGE and DREAMS OF THE GOLDEN AGE, and has written some terrific stand-alone historicals for my anthologies DANGEROUS WOMEN and ROGUES.\r\n\r\nAn amazing writer, an amazing person.&nbsp; Come meet her Monday night at 7pm, at the Jean Cocteau.","ditemid":401118,"eventtime":"2015-01-08 11:55:00","props":{"current_mood":"cheerful","current_location":"Santa Fe","taglist":"wild cards, jean cocteau, fantasy, signings, signed books","current_moodid":125,"homepage_reposted":63986505,"commentalter":1421006377,"opt_lockcomments":1,"crosspost_tw":"Carrie Is Coming http://j.mp/1y400j2","picture_keyword":"Spain","opt_screening":"F","revnum":1,"interface":"web","personifi_tags":"nterms:yes","langs":"{\"languages\":[[\"eng\",0.677510934492329]],\"detector\":\"Lingua-YALI:0.015\",\"updated\":1420916173}","revtime":1421348247},"can_comment":0,"logtime":"2015-01-10 18:55:38","anum":222,"url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/401118.html","event_timestamp":1420718100,"reply_count":3,"comments":[{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/65182618/86902","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/401118.html?thread=20081374#t20081374","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/401118.html?thread=20081374#t20081374","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/401118.html?thread=20081374#t20081374","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"shykat20","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://shykat20.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":20081374,"talkid":78442,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/401118.html?thread=20081374#t20081374","upictitle":"sunshine: shweeeeeee","article":"At no other time have I ever wished that I was in Santa Fe more.  I love love love the Kitty books, and Carrie Vaughn is one of the nicest people ever on facebook.<br /><br />When my husband and I were at the signing in MA for A Dance with Dragons, I was so tempted to ask if she is as cool as she seems... but I refrained and kept my comments to GoT.  My husband told me it wouldn't have been kosher to kick off the book launch with that... :-)","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"2 years ago","ctime":"January 11 2015, 01:33:16 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://shykat20.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img/userinfo_v8.svg?v=17080?v=146.10","co